The paper deals with the problem of dictionary learning, which is a common topic in machine learning and signal processing. The use of orthonormal dictionaries and Householder reflectors is a specific technique that falls under the category of linear algebra and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also discusses the sparsity of the resulting representations, which is a common theme in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The simulations presented in the paper are focused on image processing, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper proposes algorithms for learning the orthonormal dictionaries, which is a topic in optimization and numerical analysis (cs.SI).
